From 2c47c42ba82fd09b0a0a56a7702f89e62c33ac42 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Anshul Dubela <adubela@marvell.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 01:34:23 +0530
Subject: [PATCH]  ipintutil: Replace per-interface netifaces call with bulk
 `ip -json addr show` to fix `show ip int` hang at VLAN scale
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

 Issue
 `show ip int` hangs indefinitely (appears stuck in an infinite loop) on setups with 4K VLANs. The CLI must be killed with Ctrl+C.

 Root Cause
 `get_ip_intfs_in_namespace()` called `multi_asic_get_ip_intf_addr_from_ns(namespace, iface)` inside a per-interface for-loop. That function internally invoked `netifaces. ifaddresses(iface)` wrapped in `pyroute2.netns.pushns/popns` — producing 4000+ sequential blocking kernel round-trips at 4K VLAN scale, making the CLI appear hung.

 The helper function `multi_asic_get_addr_info_from_ns()` — which fetches all interface addresses via a single `ip -json addr show` subprocess call — was already present   in `multi_asic.py` from a prior partial fix, but the call-site in `ipintutil` had been inadvertently reverted to the old per-interface path during a rewrite.

Signed-off-by: Anshul Dubela <adubela@marvell.com>
